<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="301" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="301">
United States, Mexico (Chiapas, Durango, Hidalgo), Guatemala, Paraguay (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.4106" author="Brown, HP" journalOrPublisher="Environmental Protection Agency, Ohio" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" refId="B24" refString="Brown, HP, 1972a. Aquatic dryopoid beetles (Coleoptera) of the United States. Biota of Freshwater ecosystems, Identification Manual No. 6. Environmental Protection Agency, Ohio, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.4106" title="Aquatic dryopoid beetles (Coleoptera) of the United States. Biota of Freshwater ecosystems, Identification Manual No. 6." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.4106" year="1972 a">Brown 1972a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Arce-Perez, R" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Mexicana" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="639 - 667" publicationUrl="https://www.redalyc.org/articulo.oa?id=57515502010" refId="B8" refString="Arce-Perez, R, Gomez-Anaya, JA, Novelo-Gutierrez, R, 2010. Coleopteros acuaticos de la zona de influencia de la Central Hidroelectrica &quot;Ing. Fernando Hiriart Balderrama&quot; (C. H. Zimapan), Hidalgo, Mexico. II. Coleoptera: Polyphaga y Myxophaga. Acta Zoologica Mexicana 26 (3): 639 - 667, https://www.redalyc.org/articulo.oa?id=57515502010" title="Coleopteros acuaticos de la zona de influencia de la Central Hidroelectrica &quot; Ing. Fernando Hiriart Balderrama &quot; (C. H. Zimapan), Hidalgo, Mexico. II. Coleoptera: Polyphaga y Myxophaga." url="https://www.redalyc.org/articulo.oa?id=57515502010" volume="26" year="2010">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Arce-Pérez">Arce-Perez</normalizedToken>
et al. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
; Shepard and Aguilar-Julio 2010). The known altitude records of the species are 1,590 and 2,438 m (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.4106" author="Brown, HP" journalOrPublisher="Environmental Protection Agency, Ohio" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" refId="B24" refString="Brown, HP, 1972a. Aquatic dryopoid beetles (Coleoptera) of the United States. Biota of Freshwater ecosystems, Identification Manual No. 6. Environmental Protection Agency, Ohio, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.4106" title="Aquatic dryopoid beetles (Coleoptera) of the United States. Biota of Freshwater ecosystems, Identification Manual No. 6." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.4106" year="1972 a">Brown 1972a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Arce-Perez, R" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Mexicana" pageId="0" pageNumber="301" pagination="639 - 667" publicationUrl="https://www.redalyc.org/articulo.oa?id=57515502010" refId="B8" refString="Arce-Perez, R, Gomez-Anaya, JA, Novelo-Gutierrez, R, 2010. Coleopteros acuaticos de la zona de influencia de la Central Hidroelectrica &quot;Ing. Fernando Hiriart Balderrama&quot; (C. H. Zimapan), Hidalgo, Mexico. II. Coleoptera: Polyphaga y Myxophaga. Acta Zoologica Mexicana 26 (3): 639 - 667, https://www.redalyc.org/articulo.oa?id=57515502010" title="Coleopteros acuaticos de la zona de influencia de la Central Hidroelectrica &quot; Ing. Fernando Hiriart Balderrama &quot; (C. H. Zimapan), Hidalgo, Mexico. II. Coleoptera: Polyphaga y Myxophaga." url="https://www.redalyc.org/articulo.oa?id=57515502010" volume="26" year="2010">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Arce-Pérez">Arce-Perez</normalizedToken>
et al. 2010
</bibRefCitation>
). Herein, specimens were found at levels 1 (670 m), 2 (934 m), and 3 (1126-1194 m).
</paragraph>
